RISING actress and film producer, OT Bolts was all smiles as she premiered her new flick, Rising Sun, amidst pomp and glee. The premiere, which was held at the Blue Pictures Cinema, Onikan, Lagos State Last weekend witnessed a gathering of movie stars and entertainment stakeholders who turned up to support producer cum actress, OT Bolts as she premiered her latest flick, Rising Sun held at Blue Pictures Cinema, Onikan, Lagos State had celebrities like  Ayo Balogun, Bukola Adeeyo, Moyin Olutayo, Remmy Shitta-Bey, Seyi Edun, and Ricardo Agbor in attendance.   ONYEKA ONWENU: I see my children as prized possession     Omo Tosan takes Koredianx high up music charts     The Rise of Igbinogun premieres, gets StarTimes backing   OT Bolts, who has 40 films to her credit as a producer, also bagged an endorsement deal with TBN Food Industries Limited, makers of Top Soya Oil. She described her journey in life and career as one that is filled with the grace of God. Directed by Sesan Alabi, ‘Rising Sun’ features Jibola Dabur, Ifeanyi Kalu, Peggy Ovire, Moyinoluwa Olutayo, Blessing Onwukwe and tells the story of Ore, who stood for truth and love as she is portrayed as the only pillar that could bring peace among other tribes.